4️⃣ Self Introduction Summary (Use This in Interviews)

This is a clean 60-second answer.

You can say:

I worked on a GitOps-based DevOps project where I automated the full infrastructure and application deployment pipeline on AWS.

Infrastructure is provisioned using Terraform, which creates the VPC, subnets, IAM roles, EKS cluster, worker nodes, and an ECR repository.

I implemented CI using GitHub Actions, where the pipeline builds a Docker image for the application, tags it using the Git commit SHA, and pushes it to Amazon ECR. The pipeline also updates the Helm chart values with the new image tag.

For deployment I used Argo CD as a GitOps controller. Argo CD continuously monitors the Git repository and automatically deploys the Helm chart to the Kubernetes cluster whenever the repository changes.

The Helm chart creates the Kubernetes Deployment, Service, and Ingress resources. The Ingress is handled by the AWS Load Balancer Controller, which automatically provisions an Application Load Balancer to expose the application externally.

This setup demonstrates a complete GitOps pipeline where Git acts as the single source of truth and deployments are fully automated.

